<h2 id="section-top">Haematology</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1063">The Royal Marsden NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address"><br/>020 8661 3670</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent9a28d18a7e3e42e68a94a6445053253e">
</div>
<p>The Haemato-oncology Unit offers state-of-the-art diagnoses and treatment of  all cancers of the blood and lymphatic system. These include myeloma, lymphomas,  Hodgkin’s disease, chronic lymphatic leukaemia, and acute and chronic  leukaemias.</p>
<p>Services are provided through disease-specific clinics and a specialised  inpatient unit for the delivery of more intensive chemotherapy and bone marrow  transplantation.</p>
<p>The 32-bed inpatient unit has 20 single rooms with filtered-air protected  environments for patients that require intensive chemotherapy and bone marrow  transplantation. There is also a newly refurbished outpatient area.</p>
<p>The Unit has a high profile with all major relevant international bodies, and  collaborates in national and international trials.</p>
<p>More information can be found on our <a href="http://www.royalmarsden.nhs.uk/consultants-teams-wards/clinical-units/pages/haemato-oncology-unit.aspx">website</a>.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
